cs.NE, cs.DS, cs.DM, cs.AI, cs.CC 

This paper discusses a fitness-level model of a non-elitist mutation-only genetic algorithm with tournament selection. The paper focuses on the expected proportion of individuals with fitness above given thresholds, which is a common topic in the field of evolutionary computation. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). 

The paper also uses probability distributions and Markov chains to obtain lower bounds on expected proportions of sufficiently fit individuals, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics). 

Additionally, the paper discusses the runtime of an Iterated version of the GA on 2-SAT problem and on a family of Set Cover problems, which indicates that it could also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.CC (Computational Complexity).
